<TITLE> Australia win toss, bat first against India </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 SYDNEY, Feb 17 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Australia captain Ricky Ponting won the toss and elected to bat first in Sunday's tri-series one-day international against India at Adelaide Oval. Australia rested fast bowler Brett Lee with Stuart Clark called in to form a three-man seam attack with Mitchell Johnson and Nathan Bracken. Batsman Michael Clarke passed a fitness test after recovering from a rib injury. India brought in Munaf Patel in place of injured batsman Virender Sehwag. Australia: Ricky Ponting (captain), Adam Gilchrist, Matthew Hayden, Michael Clarke, Mike Hussey, James Hopes, Andrew Symonds, Brad Hogg, Mitchell Johnson, Nathan Bracken and Stuart Clark. India: Mahendra Singh Dhoni (captain), Sachin Tendulkar, Gautam Gambhir, Yuvraj Singh, Robin Uthappa, Rohit Sharma, Irfan Pathan, Harbhajan Singh, Shantha Sreesanth, Ishant Sharma and Munaf Pate
